[2] Tyrol, cattle
Date: Mon 7 Mar 2016
Source: Nachrichten (Austria) [in German, trans. Sabine Zentis, edited]
http://www.nachrichten.at/nachrichten/chronik/Sechs-Tiroler-Hoefe-wegen-Rinder-TBC-gesperrt;art58,2169443


Six cattle farms in Tirol under TB restrictions
-----------------------------------------------
After TB was detected on farms in Vorarlberg, now 6 cattle holdings in Tirol [Tyrol] are under restrictions. 2 holdings are located in the district of Landeck and 2 in Ausserfern.

According to Paul Ortner of the district veterinary office, there are confirmed cases of tuberculosis as well as suspects. So far, testing in Landeck revealed 3 positive animals.

The disease was detected in the early stages, while a case in Vorarlberg had open lesions.

All animals tested positive are from a region bordering Vorarlberg or have been grazing in Vorarlberg last summer.

