[3] Vorarlberg, TB testing of hunters
Date: Fri 26 Feb 2016
Source: Vorarlberg Radio (Austria) [in German, trans. Sabine Zentis, edited]
http://vorarlberg.orf.at/news/stories/2759985/


Hunters are tested for tuberculosis
-----------------------------------
After several cases of TB have been detected in cattle over the last weeks, 19 hunters will be tested as a precaution. According to the health authorities this is a routine measure.

The hunters in question are from TB affected regions and had been in contact with red deer (shooting, cutting up carcasses). They have to undergo a blood test.

The reason for surveillance is a case of clinical disease of a cow resulting in the depopulation of the holding.

