[4] Vorarlberg, hunting season regulated
Date: Fri 19 Feb 2016
Source: Vorarlberg Online (Austria) [in German, trans. Sabine Zentis, edited]
http://www.vol.at/rinder-tbc-und-rotwild-jaeger-gehen-frueher-auf-die-pirsch-landwirte-erfreut/4628851


Josef Moosbrucker, president of the chamber of agriculture, is pleased that the hunting community will help to combat TB and increase shooting of TB infected red deer.

"I thank (head of county hunters) Reinhard Metzler for his clear statement," said Moosbrugger on Friday [19 Feb 2016], referring to the announcements Metzler made on Vorarlberg Today.

Hunters start hunting deer in March [2016]
------------------------------------------
The head of Vorarlberg hunters had stated in the interview that a "massive intervention" was necessary to deal with the TB infected deer population and announced measures. Among other things, the hunting season will start much earlier this spring [2016]: in March already.

"That's of the utmost importance for the grazing period. A smaller red deer population will reduce the contact between cattle and deer, and thus also the risk of infection."

Moosbrugger hopes that with joint efforts the TB situation will improve.

Metzler announced that in addition to the earlier start of the hunting season, no age restrictions will be in place. In practice, this means that every deer, regardless of age or sex, can be shot.

Hunters are increasingly under fire since it was revealed that the hunting quotas are not met, especially in the TB hotspot areas such as in Silbertal. Deer are the main hosts of the disease; almost every 4th animal is infected.

So far the worst case this year [2016] was culling out of a farm in Bartholomaeberg last Monday [15 Feb 2016?], where the entire stock of 18 animals had to be killed. This year 9 farms were already affected, 6 of which were completely restricted.

--
